By Raji Rasak Badagry (Lagos State), – The Police on Tuesday arraigned a 27-year-old man, Sunkanmi Abdul-Hafiz in a Badagry Chief Magistrates’ Court for alleged theft of a cell phone valued at N150,000. The defendant, whose address is unknown, is standing trial on a two-count charge of stealing and breach of peace for which he pleaded not guilty. The Prosecutor, ASP. Ikem Uko told the court that the defendant committed the offence in 2020 at Benue Plaza, BBA Trade Fair Complex, Lagos. Uko said the defendant allegedly stole one Vivo Android phone valued at N150,000 belonging to Chidiebere Ogbuowa, the complainant. He said the defendant conducted himself in a manner likely to cause breach of peace by unlawfully stealing the phone. “The defendant disappeared for more than two years and only came back to the venue and was arrested by the Police. “The offences contravened Sections 287 and 168 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015,’’ he said. The Chief Magistrate, Mr Patrick Adekomaiya, granted the defendant bail in the sum of N50,000 with one surety in like sum. Adekomaiya adjourned the case until Feb.13, for mention. (NAN)